<StackPanel xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation">
	<TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,5,0,5">This is a normal paragraph:</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New">This is a code block.</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,5,0,5">Here is an example of AppleScript:</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New">tell application "Foo"<LineBreak />    beep<LineBreak />end tell</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,5,0,5">Fenced code block:</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New">&lt;div class="footer"&gt;<LineBreak />    &amp;copy; 2004 Foo Corporation<LineBreak />&lt;/div&gt;</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,5,0,5">Fenced code block (with syntax highlighting):</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New"><LineBreak />10 PRINT "*";<LineBreak /><LineBreak />20 GOTO 10<LineBreak /></TextBlock>
	<TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,5,0,5">Headers can also be written on a single line, prefixing them with hash signs (<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontFamily="Courier New">#</TextBlock>) and a space character. The number of hash signs defines the level of the header:</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New"># First level header<LineBreak /><LineBreak />## Second level header<LineBreak /><LineBreak />### Third level header<LineBreak /><LineBreak />#### Fourth level header<LineBreak /><LineBreak />...</TextBlock>
	<TextBlock xml:space="preserve" TextWrapping="NoWrap" Margin="0,5,0,5" FontFamily="Courier New">```<LineBreak />&lt;div class="footer"&gt;<LineBreak />    &amp;copy; 2004 Foo Corporation<LineBreak />&lt;/div&gt;<LineBreak />```</TextBlock>
